-- German Stocks Fall; SAP, K+S, Metro Slide as Allianz, Deutsche Bank Climb
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2011-12-21T12:54:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/german-stocks-fall-sap-k-s-metro-slide-as-allianz-deutsche-bank-climb.html
German stocks erased gains as
 SAP AG (SAP)  and  Metro AG (MEO)  declined.   The DAX Index lost 0.6 percent to 5,813.81  at 1:52 p.m. in  Frankfurt, erasing an earlier gain of as much as 2 percent.
The benchmark measure has retreated 16 percent this year amid
concern the debt crisis will derail the global economic
recovery. The broader HDAX Index also slid 0.6 percent today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tom Stoukas at 
 astoukas@bloomberg.net  